  "prompt": "Is there any dual SIM mobile supporting 4G or 4G and 3G?",
  "response": "Yes, there are many dual SIM mobile phones available in the market that support 4G or a combination of 4G and 3G. These phones allow you to use two SIM cards simultaneously, with at least one of them capable of connecting to 4G networks while the other may support 3G or 4G, depending on the phone's specifications.\n\nHere are some key points to consider:\n\n### 1. **Dual SIM 4G + 4G**\n   - Many modern smartphones support dual 4G, meaning both SIM cards can connect to 4G networks simultaneously (though only one can typically use 4G data at a time).\n   - Examples of phones with dual 4G support include the Samsung Galaxy A series, Xiaomi Redmi/Note series, Realme phones, and many others.\n\n### 2. **Dual SIM 4G + 3G**\n   - Some older or mid-range phones may support 4G on one SIM and 3G on the other.\n   - These phones are still functional but may not offer the same dual 4G capability as newer models.\n\n### 3. **Hybrid Dual SIM**\n   - Some phones come with a hybrid SIM slot, where one slot can be used for a SIM card, and the other can be used for either a second SIM or a microSD card.\n\n### Popular Dual SIM Phone Brands:\n   - **Samsung**: Galaxy A series, Galaxy M series\n   - **Xiaomi**: Redmi, Note, and Poco series\n   - **Oppo/Realme**: Various mid-range and budget models\n   - **Apple**: Dual SIM via eSIM + physical SIM (e.g., iPhone 14 series)\n\n### Things to Keep in Mind:\n   - **Network Compatibility**: Ensure the phone supports the bands used by your carrier.\n   - **Dual Standby**: Most dual SIM phones support dual standby, meaning both SIMs are active for calls and texts, but only one can use data at a time.\n   - **eSIM**: Some newer phones support eSIM technology, allowing you to have a second SIM without a physical card.\n\nIf you're looking for a specific model, let me know your budget and preferred brand, and I can suggest some options!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
